remarks: "Festino", one of the syllogisms of Aristotelian logic.  No ` ph ` is ` ps ` , and some ` ch ` is ` ps ` , therefore some ` ch ` is not ` ph ` .  (In Aristotelian notation, EIO-2:  PeM and SiM therefore SoP.) (Contributed by David A. Wheeler, 25-Nov-2016.)
statement:
festino.maj $e |- A. x ( ph -> -. ps ) $.
festino.min $e |- E. x ( ch /\ ps ) $.
festino $p |- E. x ( ch /\ -. ph ) $.
